1. e4 {JvR} e6 2. d4 d5 3. Nc3 Nf6 4. Bg5 Bb4 5. Nge2 {JvR: '!?'} dxe4 6. a3 Be7 7. Bxf6 gxf6 {JvR: '!?' Heute spielt man doch eher 7...xf6.} (7... Bxf6 {JvR} 8. Nxe4 {tempo on the bishop} e5 9. Qd3 exd4 10. Nxf6+ Qxf6 11. Qxd4 Qxd4 12. Nxd4 Bd7 13. Nb5 $14 {Minev}) 8. Nxe4 f5 {?!} (8... b6 $142 9. N2c3 Bb7 10. Qf3 c6 11. O-O-O Nd7 12. Qg3 Qb8 {! = Keres}) 9. N4c3 {!} (9. N4g3 {!?}) (9. Nd2 {?!} b6 10. c3 Bb7 11. Qc2 Nd7 12. O-O-O Nf6 13. f3 (13. Nf4) 13... Qd6 $15 {Schwarz}) 9... Bd7 $6 {? Noch eine Ungenauigkeit; Schwarz sollte 6 und b6 spielen, um auf jeden Fall das Feld d5 zu kontrollieren.} (9... b6 10. g3 Bb7 11. d5 {!} Bxd5 12. Nxd5 Qxd5 13. Qxd5 exd5 14. Bh3 $16 {! Suetin}) (9... Bf6) 10. Qd2 Bd6 (10... Bc6 11. O-O-O {'with the idea' 12.d5}) 11. O-O-O Qe7 {JvR: '24: Security of the King: 'It is clear that Black's formation is not a particularly fortunate one. After accepting the doubled f-pawns his first obligation was to take steps against a possible Pd5 by White. The simplest way would have been by means of ... Pb6, ... Bb7, followed by ... Pc6; and the indicated place for the King is the Queenside'' ?} (11... c6 12. Ng3 Qh4 13. Qe1 Kd8 {'with the idea' 14... a5, 15... Na6 Alekhine}) (11... Qf6 {!?} 12. Kb1 O-O 13. g3 Rd8 14. Bg2 c6 $14) 12. Ng3 {JvR: '!?' ! 'with the idea' 13.Nf5 ef 14.Re1 Be6 15.d5$16; 12.g3!? Qf6 13.Bg2 c6 14.Kb1 Na6 15.Rhe1 0-0-0 16.f4$14} Qh4 {JvR: '!'} (12... Z0 {JvR} 13. Nxf5 exf5 14. Re1 Be6 15. d5 {The open centre files would portend grave peril for the Black King}) 13. Qe1 {JvR: '!' JvR: '24: Security of the King: 'Not only defending against Black's ... Bf4, but also renewing his own threat of Nxf5''} (13. Kb1 {!?} O-O 14. d5 Bf4 15. Qd4) 13... Nc6 {JvR: '?'} (13... Qf4+ 14. Kb1 Nc6 {JvR: '(Alekhine)' ''} 15. Nb5 $16) ({Less risks are taken by} 13... O-O {JvR !?} 14. d5 Re8 15. Be2 a5 16. Kb1 Na6 17. dxe6 fxe6 18. Nb5 $14) 14. Nxf5 $1 {!} Qf4+ 15. Ne3 Nxd4 16. g3 Qe5 17. Bg2 {JvR: 'White exerts distant pressure by his queen and bishop.'} Nc6 {JvR: '?'} (17... Bc6 18. f4 (18. Bxc6+ {JvR} Nxc6 19. f4 Qg7 20. Nf5 Qf8 21. Nxd6+ cxd6 22. Nb5 O-O-O 23. Qc3 $1 {Fork ... exhibits power of the Queen '' Alekhine} Kb8 24. Nxd6 Rxd6 25. Rxd6 Qxd6 26. Qxh8+) 18... Qg7 (18... Qf6 19. Bxc6+ Nxc6 20. Ne4 $14) 19. Bxc6+ bxc6 20. Nc4 Rd8 21. Qe4 c5 22. Qb7 O-O 23. Rhe1 $16) ({JvR: 'The ending after'} 17... O-O-O $5 {JvR: '(Alekhine)' !?} 18. f4 (18. Nc4 {JvR} Qxe1 (18... Qg7) 19. Rhxe1 Nf5 {offers chances of survival.}) 18... Qg7 19. Nc4 Bc5 20. Na5 Bc6 21. Nxc6 Nxc6 22. Bxc6 bxc6 23. Qe4 Kb7 $16 {und Schwarz verbleibt auch hier mit einer sehr undankbaren Stellung.}) 18. f4 (18. Nc4 {!} Qh5 19. Nxd6+ cxd6 20. Rxd6 O-O-O 21. f4 e5 22. Qe4 $18) 18... Qg7 {?} (18... Qh5 {!} 19. Ne4 Be7 20. Nd5 O-O-O) 19. Nb5 {JvR: '!' '+-'} (19. Nf5 {JvR} Bxf4+ {Move order is important}) 19... O-O {JvR: 'Black has to lose a pawn. 24: Security of the King: 'At long last the Black king finds a safer place, but at the cost of a pawn, and now White holds the advantage positionally''} (19... O-O-O {!? Alekhine} 20. Bxc6 Bxc6 21. Nxa7+ Kb8 22. Nxc6+ bxc6 23. Nc4 $16) (19... Ke7 $4 20. Nf5+ $18) (19... Qf8 {JvR} 20. Nf5) 20. Nxd6 cxd6 21. Rxd6 Rfd8 22. Qd2 Be8 23. Rd1 (23. Nc4 $1 {wäre auch sehr stark gewesen.} Rxd6 24. Nxd6 Rd8 25. Rd1 $16 {mit drückender weißer Übermacht.}) 23... Rdc8 $2 {JvR: '24: Security of the King: 'With some remote hope of counterplay on the c-file, but White's attack on the other flank is much too fast''} (23... Rxd6 24. Qxd6 Rc8 {wäre noch das kleinere Übel gewesen.} (24... Rd8 25. Qc5 Rxd1+ 26. Nxd1 a6 $16 27. Ne3 f6 28. Qd6 Qf7 29. Ng4 $18)) 24. f5 {JvR: '!' Alle weißen Figuren nehmen am Kampf teil, die Triplierung in der d-Linie wirkt bedrohlich, während der schwarze a8 sowie der e8 totes Holz sind.} e5 (24... Nd8 25. Kb1 Qg5 26. Qd4 exf5 27. Qe5 Nc6 28. Bxc6 Bxc6 29. Nxf5 $18) 25. f6 Qf8 (25... Qg5 26. h4 Qh6 (26... Qxg3 27. Nf5 Qg6 28. Bxc6 Qxf5 29. Bxb7 $18) 27. Nf5 Qxd2+ 28. R1xd2 $16) 26. Nf5 {JvR: '24: Security of the King: 'Logical way to bring two pieces into the attack''} Kh8 27. Qg5 Rc7 $2 (27... a6) (27... Rd8 {JvR} 28. Rxd8 Rxd8 29. Rxd8 Nxd8 30. Ne7 {winning a second pawn}) {[%tqu "De","Wie wickelt Weiss zum Gewinn ab?","Werden Sie eine Figur los!","","g2c6","Yeah ! Korrekte Fortsetzung...",10]} 28. Bxc6 $1 {!} Rxc6 (28... Bxc6 {JvR} 29. Rd8 Rxd8 30. Rxd8) 29. Rd8 Rcc8 (29... Rac8 {JvR} 30. Qg7+ Qxg7 31. fxg7+ Kg8 32. Ne7+ {1-0 (32) Lasker-Reti New York 1924 [24: Security of the King]}) 30. Qg7+ {JvR: '!'} (30. Rxc8 Rxc8 31. Qg7+ Qxg7 32. fxg7+ Kg8 33. Ne7+ Kxg7 34. Nxc8 $18) 30... Qxg7 31. fxg7+ Kg8 32. Ne7+ (32. Rxc8 $18) 1-0


