1. d4 {Alechin:New York 1924. Lopez : 'Marshall (White) starts with a good opening pawn move. He now controls both without c5 and e5 and he releases the dark-square Bishop.''Marshall (White) starts with a good opening pawn move. He now controls both without c5 and e5 and he releases the dark-square Bishop. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Alechin:New York 1924. Lopez : 'Marshall (White) starts with a good opening pawn move. He now controls both without c5 and e5 and he releases the dark-square Bishop.'''} Nf6 {Lopez : 'Reti (Black) counters by developing the Knight to its best opening square. By without doing so, he also keeps his choice of opening a secret to White, who doesn't without know if Black will develop his Bishops through the center or the flanks.''Reti (Black) counters by developing the Knight to its best opening square. By without doing so, he also keeps his choice of opening a secret to White, who doesn't without know if Black will develop his Bishops through the center or the flanks. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'Reti (Black) counters by developing the Knight to its best opening square. By without doing so, he also keeps his choice of opening a secret to White, who doesn't without know if Black will develop his Bishops through the center or the flanks.'''} 2. Nf3 {Lopez : 'White develops the Knight toward the center, controls d4, and strengthens his without grip on e5.''White develops the Knight toward the center, controls d4, and strengthens his without grip on e5. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'White develops the Knight toward the center, controls d4, and strengthens his without grip on e5.'''} g6 {Lopez : 'Now Marshall knows that Reti intends to develop the f8-Bishop by without fianchettoing it to g7.''Now Marshall knows that Reti intends to develop the f8-Bishop by without fianchettoing it to g7. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'Now Marshall knows that Reti intends to develop the f8-Bishop by without fianchettoing it to g7.'''} 3. c4 {Lopez : 'This pawn advance carves out some more of the center for White. Also, the b1- without Knight can develop to c3 without blocking the c-pawn, and the Queen has the without option to develop along the a4-d1 diagonal.''This pawn advance carves out some more of the center for White. Also, the b1- without Knight can develop to c3 without blocking the c-pawn, and the Queen has the without option to develop along the a4-d1 diagonal. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'This pawn advance carves out some more of the center for White. Also, the b1- without Knight can develop to c3 without blocking the c-pawn, and the Queen has the without option to develop along the a4-d1 diagonal.'''} Bg7 {Lopez : 'In the Hypermodern style, Reti chooses to attack White's center from the without flank rather than fight it out in the center with his d- and e-pawns. Once without the f6- Knight moves, the Bishop will attack White's d4-pawn.''In the Hypermodern style, Reti chooses to attack White's center from the without flank rather than fight it out in the center with his d- and e-pawns. Once without the f6- Knight moves, the Bishop will attack White's d4-pawn. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'In the Hypermodern style, Reti chooses to attack White's center from the without flank rather than fight it out in the center with his d- and e-pawns. Once without the f6- Knight moves, the Bishop will attack White's d4-pawn.'''} 4. Nc3 {Lopez : 'Marshall gets the other Knight off of the back rank and into the game. Notice without how his pieces and pawns exercise control over all four center squares without (d4,e4, d5,e5).''Marshall gets the other Knight off of the back rank and into the game. Notice without how his pieces and pawns exercise control over all four center squares without (d4,e4, d5,e5). Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'Marshall gets the other Knight off of the back rank and into the game. Notice without how his pieces and pawns exercise control over all four center squares without (d4,e4, d5,e5).'''} O-O {Lopez : 'Reti completes his Kingside development. Now his King is safely tucked away without and his Rook is developed toward the important center files.''Reti completes his Kingside development. Now his King is safely tucked away without and his Rook is developed toward the important center files. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'Reti completes his Kingside development. Now his King is safely tucked away without and his Rook is developed toward the important center files.'''} 5. e4 {Lopez : 'Since Reti is allowing him to develop in the center, Marshall builds up an without imposing pawn phalanx by advancing the e-pawn.''Since Reti is allowing him to develop in the center, Marshall builds up an without imposing pawn phalanx by advancing the e-pawn. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'Since Reti is allowing him to develop in the center, Marshall builds up an without imposing pawn phalanx by advancing the e-pawn.'''} d6 {Lopez : 'This pawn advance prevents White from advancing either his Knight or pawn to without e5, prepares for a possible later e7-e5 pawn push for Black, and releases without the c8-Bishop from captivity.''This pawn advance prevents White from advancing either his Knight or pawn to without e5, prepares for a possible later e7-e5 pawn push for Black, and releases without the c8-Bishop from captivity. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'This pawn advance prevents White from advancing either his Knight or pawn to without e5, prepares for a possible later e7-e5 pawn push for Black, and releases without the c8-Bishop from captivity.'''} 6. Bd3 {Lopez : 'Marshall develops his light-square Bishop and gets ready to castle. But the without Bishop blocks the Queen's protection of the d4-pawn, which weakens the pawn without slightly. Perhaps 6.Be2 might have been better.''Marshall develops his light-square Bishop and gets ready to castle. But the without Bishop blocks the Queen's protection of the d4-pawn, which weakens the pawn without slightly. Perhaps 6.Be2 might have been better. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'Marshall develops his light-square Bishop and gets ready to castle. But the without Bishop blocks the Queen's protection of the d4-pawn, which weakens the pawn without slightly. Perhaps 6.Be2 might have been better.'''} (6. Be2 {This looks a little better than what was actually played by Marshall. It's without heartening to know that even the greats slip up once in a while! Maybe now without we won't be so hard on ourselves when we make mistakes in our own games!}) 6... Bg4 {Lopez : 'Reti's keen eye spots the d4-pawn's weakness and siezes the moment to exploit without it by pinning the f3-Knight. Now the poor pawn is totally unprotected! White without is forced to expend a tempo to protect it, or else...''Reti's keen eye spots the d4-pawn's weakness and siezes the moment to exploit without it by pinning the f3-Knight. Now the poor pawn is totally unprotected! White without is forced to expend a tempo to protect it, or else... Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'Reti's keen eye spots the d4-pawn's weakness and siezes the moment to exploit without it by pinning the f3-Knight. Now the poor pawn is totally unprotected! White without is forced to expend a tempo to protect it, or else...'''} 7. h3 {Lopez : '...drive the Bishop away. Now the Bishop is forced to either withdraw or without capture the Knight. This pawn attack is called "putting the question to the without Bishop".''...drive the Bishop away. Now the Bishop is forced to either withdraw or without capture the Knight. This pawn attack is called "putting the question to the without Bishop". Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : '...drive the Bishop away. Now the Bishop is forced to either withdraw or without capture the Knight. This pawn attack is called "putting the question to the without Bishop".'''} Bxf3 {Lopez : 'Reti decides to trade his Bishop for the Knight, insuring that the d4-pawn without will remain weak and unprotected, at least for a while.''Reti decides to trade his Bishop for the Knight, insuring that the d4-pawn without will remain weak and unprotected, at least for a while. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'Reti decides to trade his Bishop for the Knight, insuring that the d4-pawn without will remain weak and unprotected, at least for a while.'''} 8. Qxf3 {Lopez : 'Marshall recaptures with the Queen, developing it in the process. This is without much better than doubling up pawns on the f-file with 8.gxf3. But now the without d-pawn stands alone...''Marshall recaptures with the Queen, developing it in the process. This is without much better than doubling up pawns on the f-file with 8.gxf3. But now the without d-pawn stands alone... Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'Marshall recaptures with the Queen, developing it in the process. This is without much better than doubling up pawns on the f-file with 8.gxf3. But now the without d-pawn stands alone...'''} (8. gxf3 {The f-pawns and h3-pawn are weak because they can't be defended by other without pawns. Black should now shift his attack to the Kingside to exploit the without half- open g-file and the weak pawns.}) 8... Nfd7 {Lopez : '...so Reti unleashes a discovered attack against it (from the g7-Bishop). without Despite the fact that he lags behind in development, Black still controls without the game by continuing to make threats which must be answered by without White.''...so Reti unleashes a discovered attack against it (from the g7-Bishop). without Despite the fact that he lags behind in development, Black still controls without the game by continuing to make threats which must be answered by without White. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : '...so Reti unleashes a discovered attack against it (from the g7-Bishop). without Despite the fact that he lags behind in development, Black still controls without the game by continuing to make threats which must be answered by without White.'''} (8... Nc6) 9. Be3 {Lopez : 'Marshall protects the weak pawn and usefully develops his last minor piece at without the same time.''Marshall protects the weak pawn and usefully develops his last minor piece at without the same time. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'Marshall protects the weak pawn and usefully develops his last minor piece at without the same time.'''} c5 {Lopez : 'Reti hits the weak pawn a second time. How in the world will Marshall defend without it now?''Reti hits the weak pawn a second time. How in the world will Marshall defend without it now? Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'Reti hits the weak pawn a second time. How in the world will Marshall defend without it now?'''} (9... Nc6) 10. d5 {Lopez : 'He defends the pawn by advancing it! Now it's amply protected by two fellow without pawns and a Knight. At the same time he grabs more space on Black's side of without the board. Now c6 and e6 are unusable by Black.''He defends the pawn by advancing it! Now it's amply protected by two fellow without pawns and a Knight. At the same time he grabs more space on Black's side of without the board. Now c6 and e6 are unusable by Black. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'He defends the pawn by advancing it! Now it's amply protected by two fellow without pawns and a Knight. At the same time he grabs more space on Black's side of without the board. Now c6 and e6 are unusable by Black.'''} Ne5 {Lopez : 'The Knight leaps ahead and forks the Queen and light-square Bishop. See how without Reti continues to make threats and keep the initiative.''The Knight leaps ahead and forks the Queen and light-square Bishop. See how without Reti continues to make threats and keep the initiative. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'The Knight leaps ahead and forks the Queen and light-square Bishop. See how without Reti continues to make threats and keep the initiative.'''} (10... Bxc3+ 11. bxc3 Qa5) (10... a6 11. a4 Qb6 12. Qe2 Ne5 13. Bc1 Nbd7 14. a5 Qb3 (14... Qb4 15. Ra4 Nxd3+ 16. Qxd3 Bxc3+) 15. Ra3 Nxd3+ 16. Qxd3 Qb4 17. Ra4 Bxc3+) 11. Qe2 {Lopez : 'The White Queen retreats and simultaneously protects the menaced wi