t it. It also sets up an "invisible barrier" on the d-file which White's King without cannot enter or cross.''The Rook shifts position to another square where the c5-pawn still defends without it. It also sets up an "invisible barrier" on the d-file which White's King without cannot enter or cross. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'The Rook shifts position to another square where the c5-pawn still defends without it. It also sets up an "invisible barrier" on the d-file which White's King without cannot enter or cross.'''} (30... Rb3+ 31. Kf2 Rd3 32. Re1 f5) 31. g4 {Lopez : 'Since his activity is now limited on the Queenside, Marshall advances his without g-pawn to grab more space on the Kingside.''Since his activity is now limited on the Queenside, Marshall advances his without g-pawn to grab more space on the Kingside. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'Since his activity is now limited on the Queenside, Marshall advances his without g-pawn to grab more space on the Kingside.'''} Ke8 {Lopez : 'Reti has a choice of two plans: to counterattack with his Kingside pawns or without continue to maneuver his King toward the Queenside. He chooses the latter.''Reti has a choice of two plans: to counterattack with his Kingside pawns or without continue to maneuver his King toward the Queenside. He chooses the latter. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'Reti has a choice of two plans: to counterattack with his Kingside pawns or without continue to maneuver his King toward the Queenside. He chooses the latter.'''} (31... f5 32. exf5 gxf5 33. gxf5 Rxd5 $17) 32. Re3 {Lopez : 'Since the b2-pawn is no longer threatened, Marshall is free to prepare a without counterattack by moving his Rook.''Since the b2-pawn is no longer threatened, Marshall is free to prepare a without counterattack by moving his Rook. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'Since the b2-pawn is no longer threatened, Marshall is free to prepare a without counterattack by moving his Rook.'''} (32. g5) 32... Rb4 {Lopez : 'Reti's Rook returns to b4 and attacks the pawn again.''Reti's Rook returns to b4 and attacks the pawn again. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'Reti's Rook returns to b4 and attacks the pawn again.'''} (32... f5) 33. Ra3 {Lopez : 'Marshall, tired of being tied to defense, decides to abandon the pawn and set without up an annoying series of checks against the Black King.''Marshall, tired of being tied to defense, decides to abandon the pawn and set without up an annoying series of checks against the Black King. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'Marshall, tired of being tied to defense, decides to abandon the pawn and set without up an annoying series of checks against the Black King.'''} Rxb2 {Lopez : 'Reti wins a pawn, but allows Marshall to counterattack with the Rook.''Reti wins a pawn, but allows Marshall to counterattack with the Rook. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'Reti wins a pawn, but allows Marshall to counterattack with the Rook.'''} (33... f6) 34. Ra8+ {Lopez : 'Marshall checks Black's King and drives it off of the back rank.''Marshall checks Black's King and drives it off of the back rank. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'Marshall checks Black's King and drives it off of the back rank.'''} Kd7 {Lopez : 'The Black King flees to the only possible square. Will Marshall decide to without check again, or will he attack the Black Kingside pawns with his Rook?''The Black King flees to the only possible square. Will Marshall decide to without check again, or will he attack the Black Kingside pawns with his Rook? Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'The Black King flees to the only possible square. Will Marshall decide to without check again, or will he attack the Black Kingside pawns with his Rook?'''} 35. Ra7+ {Lopez : 'Marshall maintains the pressure by checking again.''Marshall maintains the pressure by checking again. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'Marshall maintains the pressure by checking again.'''} Kd8 {Lopez : 'The King escapes check and continues to protect the e7-pawn.''The King escapes check and continues to protect the e7-pawn. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'The King escapes check and continues to protect the e7-pawn.'''} 36. e5 {Lopez : 'The White e-pawn advances, forcing Black to capture it (if Black doesn't, without then White plays 37.exd6 exd6 38.Rxf7 and wins a pawn).''The White e-pawn advances, forcing Black to capture it (if Black doesn't, without then White plays 37.exd6 exd6 38.Rxf7 and wins a pawn). Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'The White e-pawn advances, forcing Black to capture it (if Black doesn't, without then White plays 37.exd6 exd6 38.Rxf7 and wins a pawn).'''} dxe5 {Lopez : 'Now Black is stuck with a weak, isolated pawn on c5.''Now Black is stuck with a weak, isolated pawn on c5. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'Now Black is stuck with a weak, isolated pawn on c5.'''} (36... Rb3+ 37. Ke4 Rb4+ 38. Ke3 $11 g5 39. exd6 gxf4+ 40. Kf2 exd6 41. Rxf7 Rd4 42. Rxh7 c4 43. g5 c3 $11 44. g6 Rd2+ 45. Kf3 Rd3+ 46. Ke2 (46. Kxf4 c2) 46... Rg3 47. Kd1 Rxg6 48. Rf7 $11) (36... Rb6 37. h4 h6 38. e6 $11) 37. fxe5 {Lopez : 'White recaptures to complete the pawn swap. Now, if the White Rook moves, the without squares c6,d6,e6, and f6 are covered by White's pawns and are denied to without Black's King.''White recaptures to complete the pawn swap. Now, if the White Rook moves, the without squares c6,d6,e6, and f6 are covered by White's pawns and are denied to without Black's King. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'White recaptures to complete the pawn swap. Now, if the White Rook moves, the without squares c6,d6,e6, and f6 are covered by White's pawns and are denied to without Black's King.'''} c4 {Lopez : 'Reti hopes to strengthen the pawn by advancing it to a square where it is without easily defended by the Rook. Also, remember that a passed pawn becomes more without dangerous the closer it gets to the promotion square.''Reti hopes to strengthen the pawn by advancing it to a square where it is without easily defended by the Rook. Also, remember that a passed pawn becomes more without dangerous the closer it gets to the promotion square. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'Reti hopes to strengthen the pawn by advancing it to a square where it is without easily defended by the Rook. Also, remember that a passed pawn becomes more without dangerous the closer it gets to the promotion square.'''} 38. Ke3 {Lopez : 'A centrally-posted King is a distinct advantage in the endgame. Marshall without moves his King toward the center, where it can move to the Quenside to help without attack Black's pawn, or to the Kingside to help prevent a Black pawn without breakthrough.''A centrally-posted King is a distinct advantage in the endgame. Marshall without moves his King toward the center, where it can move to the Quenside to help without attack Black's pawn, or to the Kingside to help prevent a Black pawn without breakthrough. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'A centrally-posted King is a distinct advantage in the endgame. Marshall without moves his King toward the center, where it can move to the Quenside to help without attack Black's pawn, or to the Kingside to help prevent a Black pawn without breakthrough.'''} c3 {Lopez : 'The Black pawn continues its march toward either coronation or death.''The Black pawn continues its march toward either coronation or death. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'The Black pawn continues its march toward either coronation or death.'''} 39. Ra8+ {Lopez : 'The passed c-pawn is a dangerous threat; if it manages to promote to a Queen, without White's a dead duck. Marshall is trying for a draw by perpetual check.''The passed c-pawn is a dangerous threat; if it manages to promote to a Queen, without White's a dead duck. Marshall is trying for a draw by perpetual check. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'The passed c-pawn is a dangerous threat; if it manages to promote to a Queen, without White's a dead duck. Marshall is trying for a draw by perpetual check.'''} Kc7 {Lopez : 'The Black King obviously must move to escape check.''The Black King obviously must move to escape check. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'The Black King obviously must move to escape check.'''} 40. Ra7+ {Lopez : 'Another check...''Another check... Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'Another check...'''} Kd8 {Lopez : '...and another evasion. The Black King must come back to d8 or else the without e7-pawn is lost.''...and another evasion. The Black King must come back to d8 or else the without e7-pawn is lost. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : '...and another evasion. The Black King must come back to d8 or else the without e7-pawn is lost.'''} (40... Rb7 41. Ra3 c2 42. Rc3+ Kd7 43. Rxc2 Rb3+ 44. Kd4 Rxh3 45. Ra2 h5 46. gxh5 gxh5 47. Ra7+ $11) 41. Ra8+ $11 {Lopez : 'Again, Marshall hopes to draw by either threefold repetition of position or without by perpetual check.''Again, Marshall hopes to draw by either threefold repetition of position or without by perpetual check. Alekhine,Alexander: '=' Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'Again, Marshall hopes to draw by either threefold repetition of position or without by perpetual check.'''} Kc7 {Lopez : 'The King must move again.''The King must move again. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'The King must move again.'''} 42. Ra7+ {Lopez : 'Marshall again hopes to repeat the position...''Marshall again hopes to repeat the position... Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'Marshall again hopes to repeat the position...'''} Rb7 {Lopez : 'But Reti will not draw quietly! He offers to exchange Rooks, forcing Marshall without to work for the draw.''But Reti will not draw quietly! He offers to exchange Rooks, forcing Marshall without to work for the draw. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'But Reti will not draw quietly! He offers to exchange Rooks, forcing Marshall without to work for the draw.'''} 43. Ra3 {Lopez : 'Marshall surprises Reti with this move. The Rook attacks Black's passed pawn without (which cannot now be defended!).''Marshall surprises Reti with this move. The Rook attacks Black's passed pawn without (which cannot now be defended!). Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'Marshall surprises Reti with this move. The Rook attacks Black's passed pawn without (which cannot now be defended!).'''} c2 {Lopez : 'Reti pushes the pawn, but to no avail. The pawn is marked for death.''Reti pushes the pawn, but to no avail. The pawn is marked for death. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'Reti pushes the pawn, but to no avail. The pawn is marked for death.'''} 44. Rc3+ {Lopez : 'Marshall springs a double attack (checking the King and attacking the pawn). without This assures the pawn's sad demise.''Marshall springs a double attack (checking the King and attacking the pawn). without This assures the pawn's sad demise. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'Marshall springs a double attack (checking the King and attacking the pawn). without This assures the pawn's sad demise.'''} Kd7 {Lopez : 'The Black King shuttles sideways toward its own pawns, in order to help without protect them or aid in their later advance.''The Black King shuttles sideways toward its own pawns, in order to help without protect them or aid in their later advance. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'The Black King shuttles sideways toward its own pawns, in order to help without protect them or aid in their later advance.'''} 45. Rxc2 {Lopez : 'Black's passed pawn finally gives up the ghost.''Black's passed pawn finally gives up the ghost. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'Black's passed pawn finally gives up the ghost.'''} Rb3+ {Lopez : 'Reti wins a pawn using a basic tactic: the skewer, or x-ray attack. The White without King must move out of check, after which the Black Rook pockets the without h3-pawn.''Reti wins a pawn using a basic tactic: the skewer, or x-ray attack. The White without King must move out of check, after which the Black Rook pockets the without h3-pawn. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'Reti wins a pawn using a basic tactic: the skewer, or x-ray attack. The White without King must move out of check, after which the Black Rook pockets the without h3-pawn.'''} 46. Kd4 {Lopez : 'The best place for White's King to move to. Now the King supports both of without White's center pawns.''The best place for White's King to move to. Now the King supports both of without White's center pawns. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'The best place for White's King to move to. Now the King supports both of without White's center pawns.'''} Rxh3 {Lopez : 'Reti snatches the h-pawn. Now Black is a pawn ahead, and may have chances of without creating another passed pawn.''Reti snatches the h-pawn. Now Black is a pawn ahead, and may have chances of without creating another passed pawn. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'Reti snatches the h-pawn. Now Black is a pawn ahead, and may have chances of without creating another passed pawn.'''} 47. Ra2 {Lopez : 'Since he's a pawn behind, Marshall sees slight chance of winning the game. He without again maneuvers for a draw by repetition or perpetual check.''Since he's a pawn behind, Marshall sees slight chance of winning the game. He without again maneuvers for a draw by repetition or perpetual check. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'Since he's a pawn behind, Marshall sees slight chance of winning the game. He without again maneuvers for a draw by repetition or perpetual check.'''} Rg3 {Lopez : 'Reti could have played 47...Rb3 instead (trying to get into position to offer without a Rook exchange like on move 42), but he decides to capture White's without g-pawn.''Reti could have played 47...Rb3 instead (trying to get into position to offer without a Rook exchange like on move 42), but he decides to capture White's without g-pawn. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'Reti could have played 47...Rb3 instead (trying to get into position to offer without a Rook exchange like on move 42), but he decides to capture White's without g-pawn.'''} 48. Ra7+ {Lopez : 'As expected, Marshall plays for a draw.''As expected, Marshall plays for a draw. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'As expected, Marshall plays for a draw.'''} Kd8 {Lopez : 'The King goes to the only square that still allows it to defend the without e7-pawn.''The King goes to the only square that still allows it to defend the without e7-pawn. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'The King goes to the only square that still allows it to defend the without e7-pawn.'''} 49. Ra8+ {Lopez : 'To draw, all Marshall needs to do now is keep checking the Black King.''To draw, all Marshall needs to do now is keep checking the Black King. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'To draw, all Marshall needs to do now is keep checking the Black King.'''} Kc7 {Lopez : 'Despite his material advantage and threat on the White g-pawn, all Reti can without obtain now is a draw.''Despite his material advantage and threat on the White g-pawn, all Reti can without obtain now is a draw. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'Despite his material advantage and threat on the White g-pawn, all Reti can without obtain now is a draw.'''} 50. Ra7+ {Lopez : 'Marshall checks again...''Marshall checks again... Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : 'Marshall checks again...'''} Kd8 {Lopez : '...and Reti retreats. Rather than play out the moves for a threefold- without repetition, Marshall and Reti agree to a draw.''...and Reti retreats. Rather than play out the moves for a threefold- without repetition, Marshall and Reti agree to a draw. Alekhine,Alexander: 'Lopez : '...and Reti retreats. Rather than play out the moves for a threefold- without repetition, Marshall and Reti agree to a draw.'''} 1/2-1/2


