1. e4 e5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. Bc4 Nxe4 4. Qh5 Nd6 5. Bb3 Be7 6. Qxe5 O-O 7. Nd5 Re8 8. Qh5 g6 9. Qd1 Nf5 10. Nf3 c6 11. Ne3 Nxe3 12. dxe3 d5 13. O-O b5 (13... Nd7 $142 {idea ...Nf6}) 14. e4 $1 dxe4 15. Ne5 Be6 16. Bxe6 fxe6 17. Qg4 Bf6 {#} 18. Nxg6 hxg6 19. Qxg6+ Bg7 20. Bh6 Re7 21. Bxg7 (21. Bg5 Qe8) (21. Rad1 Qe8) 21... Rxg7 22. Qxe6+ Kh8 23. Rad1 (23. Qxe4) (23. Rae1) 23... Nd7 24. Rd6 {Why not 24 Qxc6 or 24 Qxe4} Qe7 25. Re1 Qxe6 26. Rxe6 c5 27. R1xe4 c4 28. Rh6+ Kg8 29. Reh4 Rf8 30. R4h5 b4 31. Rh8+ Kf7 32. Rxf8+ Kxf8 33. Rb5 Nb6 34. Rxb4 Rd7 35. g4 Rd2 36. c3 {It looks as if White could have played on without risk. Source: Deutsche Schachzeitung 1916 p252; Sevecek & Kalendovsky p28.} 1/2-1/2


