1. c4 e5 2. Nc3 Nf6 3. Nf3 Nc6 4. e4 Bc5 5. Nxe5 Nxe5 6. d4 Bd6 $2 ({Correct is} 6... Bb4 7. dxe5 Nxe4 {(List-Colle, Berlin 1926).}) 7. c5 $1 Bxc5 8. dxe5 Ng8 9. Qg4 Kf8 10. Qg3 Ne7 11. Bc4 Ng6 12. f4 Qh4 13. Nd5 c6 14. Be3 d6 15. Bxc5 Qxg3+ 16. hxg3 dxc5 17. Ne3 b5 18. Be2 Ke7 19. O-O-O Nf8 20. Nf5+ Bxf5 21. exf5 Nd7 22. Rd6 Rac8 23. g4 h6 24. Bf3 c4 25. Bxc6 Nc5 26. Bxb5 Rhd8 27. Rxd8 Rxd8 28. Rd1 $6 (28. g3 $1 Rd3 29. g5 $1 hxg5 30. Rh8 Nd7 31. Ra8 {finishes the game.}) 28... Nd3+ 29. Kb1 Rb8 30. a4 a6 31. Bxa6 Nxb2 32. Rd4 Nxa4+ 33. Kc2 Rb2+ 34. Kc1 Rxg2 35. Rxc4 Nb6 36. Rc7+ Kf8 37. Rb7 Nd5 38. Bc4 Rg1+ 39. Kb2 $6 (39. Kd2 {wins more quickly.}) 39... Rg2+ 40. Ka3 Rg3+ 41. Ka4 $6 {Réti gets another chance.} ({Better is} 41. Bb3 $1) 41... Rxg4 $1 42. Bxd5 Rxf4+ 43. Kb5 Rxf5 44. Kc6 Rxe5 45. Rxf7+ Ke8 46. Ra7 $3 {White has sealed a remarkable move.} (46. Rxg7 Re2 47. Kd6 Rf2 $1 {leads to a theoretical draw (Szen and Berger).}) 46... Re1 ({Nimzowitsch analyses} 46... Kf8 47. Kd6 Re8 ({the point is} 47... Rf5 48. Ra8#) 48. Rd7 $3 {Zugzwang.} h5 $1 49. Rf7+ Kg8 50. Ra7+ Kf8 51. Rd7 $1 h4 52. Rf7+ Kg8 53. Ra7+ Kf8 54. Rd7 $1 {The third time becomes fatal.} h3 ({or} 54... g5 55. Rh7 Re2 56. Rf7+ Ke8 57. Rf5) 55. Rf7+ Kg8 56. Rf3+ Kh7 57. Bf7 $1 {and White wins.}) 47. Kd6 Kf8 48. Rf7+ Ke8 49. Rf2 Kd8 50. Rf8+ Re8 51. Rf7 Re1 52. Rxg7 Re2 53. Rh7 Re1 54. Rxh6 Re8 55. Rh7 Kc8 (55... Re2 56. Rg7 Re1 57. Rb7 Rc1 58. Bb3 $1 {and White wins à la Philidor.}) 56. Rc7+ Kb8 57. Rb7+ Kc8 58. Rb4 Rd8+ 59. Kc6 Re8 60. Ra4 Kb8 61. Kb6 Kc8 62. Bc6 1-0


