{JvR: 'The congress took place in the Hermann-Loge from 18 vii until 2 viii. The master event had a field like in the past. Chess benefited from the 'roaring twenties'. '} 1. e3 e5 {Opening = A28 - Englisch-Vierspringer Variante /English-Four Knight's Var} 2. c4 {JvR: 'Nimzowitsch plays the Van't Kruijs.'} Nf6 3. Nc3 Nc6 4. Nf3 Bb4 5. Be2 O-O 6. O-O Re8 {last book move} 7. a3 Bxc3 8. bxc3 d6 9. Ne1 Ne7 10. d3 c6 11. a4 Be6 12. a5 d5 13. c5 Qc7 14. Qa4 Ng6 15. Bd2 $15 (15. Rb1 Nd7 $11) 15... a6 16. g3 $17 {JvR: '?!' JvR: 'White's position becomes passive.'} (16. Rb1 e4 $11) ({Better is} 16. f3) 16... e4 {JvR: '!'} 17. d4 h5 18. Ng2 Bg4 19. f3 $17 {JvR: '?' JvR: 'Square e4 will become a weakness.'} (19. Bxg4 Nxg4 20. c4 dxc4 $11) 19... exf3 20. Bxf3 Bxf3 21. Rxf3 Ne4 {JvR: '!'} 22. Be1 Qd7 23. c4 Qg4 24. Rf1 Rad8 25. Qd1 dxc4 26. Qxg4 hxg4 27. Rc1 Ng5 {JvR: '!?'} 28. Rxc4 Nf3+ {JvR: '!?'} 29. Kh1 Rd5 {JvR: '?!'} ({Better is} 29... Ne7 $1 30. Rc2 Nd5) 30. h4 (30. Rb4 Re7 $11) 30... Rd7 31. Rc2 Ne7 32. Rcf2 $15 {JvR: '?!' JvR: 'Nimzowitsch despairs too soon.'} (32. Rb2 Nd5 $11) 32... Nd5 {[%cal Rd5e3,Re8e3,Gg2e3] Attacks the backward pawn on e3} 33. Rxf3 {JvR: '!?'} gxf3 34. Rxf3 Rde7 {[%cal Rd5e3,Re7e3,Re8e3,Gf3e3,Gg2e3] The pressure on the backward pawn e3 grows} 35. Bd2 Re4 36. Kg1 R8e6 37. Rf1 Kf8 38. Rb1 Re7 39. Kf2 Ke8 40. Rb3 Kd8 41. Ne1 R4e6 42. Nf3 Nf6 43. Ng5 Ne4+ 44. Nxe4 Rxe4 45. Kf3 f5 46. Be1 Ke8 47. Bf2 Kf7 48. Rb1 g5 49. hxg5 Kg6 50. Rf1 Rh7 51. Rb1 Kxg5 52. Rb6 Ree7 53. Rb1 Kf6 {JvR: '?!'} 54. g4 {JvR: '!'} fxg4+ {Black begins to deal mighty blows} 55. Kxg4 Ke6 56. Kf3 $17 {JvR: '?!'} (56. Bg3 {JvR: '!?'} Ref7 (56... Reg7+ 57. Kf3 Rh3 58. Rg1 Kd5 59. Rg2 Kc4 {brings insufficient relief to White.}) 57. e4 Rhg7+ 58. Kh4 Re7 $15) 56... Ref7+ 57. Kg2 Rhg7+ 58. Bg3 $19 (58. Kf1 $5 $17) 58... Kd5 59. Kh2 Ke4 (59... Rg8 60. Rg1 $19) 60. Be5 (60. Bf4 $142 $19) 60... Rg8 {The mate threat is Rh7} 61. Kh1 Rh7+ (61... Kxe3 $6 62. Rb3+ Ke4 63. Rb2 $19) 62. Bh2 Rgh8 {Threatening mate: Rxh2} (62... Rgh8 63. Kg1 Rxh2 64. Rxb7 Kxe3 $19) (62... Kxe3 $143 63. d5 Rgh8 64. Kg1 Rxh2 65. Rxb7 cxd5 66. Rb6 $19) 0-1


