{Starting out as an English Opening this game soon transposes into a main line of the Reti. Black seemed to be doing OK up to move 22 when he finally succumbed to White's ongoing pressure.} 1. c4 e6 2. g3 d5 3. Bg2 Nf6 4. Nf3 Be7 5. O-O O-O 6. b3 c5 7. cxd5 ({These days we tend to keep the central tension, say with} 7. e3) ({or} 7. Bb2 {.}) 7... Nxd5 8. Bb2 Nc6 9. Nc3 Bf6 10. Qc1 Nxc3 11. Bxc3 e5 12. d3 Rb8 {It makes sense to take the rook off the h1-a8 diagonal but more recent encounters have featured other moves:} ({a)} 12... Be6 13. Qb2 Nd4 14. e3 Nxf3+ 15. Bxf3 Bd5 16. Be4 Re8 17. Qe2 Qd6 {was dead equal in Speelman, J (2583) - Ganguly, S (2531), Bled 2002.}) ({b)} 12... Bg4 13. h3 Be6 14. Qb2 Re8 15. Nd2 Rc8 16. Ne4 Be7 17. f4 $6 f5 18. Nd2 exf4 19. Bxg7 $2 fxg3 20. Bxc6 Rxc6 21. Bh8 Bf8 {was good for Black in Dizdarevic, E (2520)-Zelcic, R (2554), Solin/Spilt 2002.}) 13. Qb2 Nd4 14. e3 Nxf3+ 15. Bxf3 Qxd3 16. Bg2 ({And not} 16. Bxe5 $2 {because of} Qf5 17. Bxf6 Qxf3 {threatening 18...Bh3.}) 16... b6 17. Bxe5 Bxe5 18. Qxe5 Bb7 (18... Bg4 {might have been better to try and keep White's rooks off the d-file, at least temporarily.}) 19. Rfd1 Qb5 20. Qc7 Bxg2 21. Kxg2 a5 22. Rd7 {White has kept an edge right into the endgame. Maybe Black could have held the game with super accurate defence but then this is never easy.} Rbc8 (22... a4 {is an interesting bid for counterplay as if White carries out his 'threat' of} 23. Rxf7 {there follows} Rxf7 24. Qxb8+ Rf8 25. Qb7 Qe2 26. Qd5+ Kh8 27. Rf1 a3 {threatening to take on a2.}) 23. Qd6 Rc6 $6 ({And here} 23... c4 {is a better chance, trying to hoover some pawns off the board.}) 24. Qd5 a4 25. Ra7 Rcc8 ({Perhaps it was only here that Black saw} 25... axb3 26. a4 {, winning the rook on c6. As a result he loses a pawn.}) 26. Rxa4 Rcd8 27. Qf3 Qd3 28. Rc4 Rd6 29. Qe4 Qe2 30. Rc2 Qb5 31. Qf3 Rfd8 32. Re1 Qd7 33. e4 Rd3 34. Re3 Rd1 35. Rce2 Qe6 36. e5 h6 37. Re4 R1d4 38. Rxd4 Rxd4 39. Re4 Rd2 40. Ra4 Qxe5 41. Ra8+ Kh7 42. Qxf7 Qe4+ 43. Qf3 Qe6 44. Rb8 Rd4 45. h4 Rd2 ({Or} 45... c4 46. bxc4 Rxc4 47. Rxb6 Qxb6 48. Qd3+ Kh8 49. Qxc4 {etc.}) 46. h5 Qe5 47. Qa8 Qd5+ 48. Qxd5 Rxd5 49. Rxb6 Rxh5 50. Rb5 Rd5 51. a4 Rd3 52. a5 1-0


