1. e4 {This game is from The Blind simul on 12 boards. Reti made mistakes typical for simuls: he often played without having a deep plan.} c5 2. Nf3 e6 3. d4 cxd4 4. Nxd4 Nf6 5. Nc3 d6 6. Be2 Be7 7. O-O O-O 8. Kh1 {White plans f2-f4 and so he removes his king from the diagonal a7-g1 to avoid inconvenience with pinning the knight on d4.} Nc6 9. f4 a6 10. Be3 Bd7 11. Bf3 ({The plan with Qe1-g3 was found later.} 11. Qe1) 11... Rc8 12. Qe1 Qc7 13. Rd1 (13. Qg3) 13... Na5 {[%cal Ya5c4] Black has disposed his pieces well and we can say that the position is approximatelly equal.} (13... b5) 14. Qf2 ({The alternatives are either a sharp} 14. g4 $5 $13) ({or the attempt of the attack on the kingside} 14. Qg3 {though it should be said that the plan with Qg3 was introduced in practice later.} Nc4 15. Bc1 $11) 14... Nc4 15. Bc1 Qb6 $2 ({The queen is not well placed here, better was} 15... b5) 16. b3 $1 Na5 17. Bb2 $2 ({Reti missed a typical The Sicilian blow by} 17. Nf5 $1 {Of course, at the time this game was played such ideas were not known.} Qd8 18. Nxe7+ Qxe7 19. Rd3 $18 {[%cal Yf1d1,Rc1a3]}) 17... Qc7 18. Nde2 b5 (18... Bc6 $5) 19. Rd2 ({Schematic play which is typical for simuls. Better was} 19. e5 $5) 19... Bc6 20. Rfd1 $6 (20. a3 $11) 20... b4 21. Nb1 Nxe4 (21... Nb7 $5 {leads to equal play.}) 22. Bxe4 Bxe4 23. Bxg7 $6 ({Again, White plays a move that is typical for simuls. Beter was} 23. Qd4 Bf6 24. Qxe4 Bxb2 25. Qxb4 {with approximatelly equal play.}) 23... Kxg7 24. Qd4+ Kg8 25. Qxe4 d5 {Though material is equal, Black stands slightly better.} 26. Qf3 Bf6 27. Ng3 Bg7 ({Better was} 27... Kh8) 28. Nh5 f5 29. Nxg7 ({Unnecessary exchange. Better was} 29. Re1) 29... Qxg7 30. Re2 Kf7 $2 (30... Rfe8 {leads to equal play.}) 31. Rde1 ({White has a clear advantage after} 31. Qe3 Qf6 32. Nd2 $1 $16 {[%csl Re5,Rg5][%cal Yd2f3,Rf3e5,Rf3g5]}) 31... Rfe8 32. Qd3 ({White should have improved the position of the knight} 32. Nd2 $5 {and now it's not good for Black to take the pawn} Rxc2 $2 33. Ne4 $16 fxe4 34. Qh5+ Qg6 35. Qxg6+ Kxg6 36. Rxc2 $16) 32... Rc6 ({Better was} 32... Nb7 33. Qxa6 Nc5 34. Qb6 Ne4 35. Qxb4 Qh6 {with unclear play.}) 33. Nd2 $1 {The knight entered the game. Due to numerous weaknesses on Black's side, this means that he is lost.} Qc3 34. Nf3 Qxd3 35. cxd3 Kf6 36. Nd4 (36. h3 $16) 36... Rb6 $2 ({This move loses. Better was} 36... Rc3 37. Re5 Rxd3 38. Nxe6 $16) 37. Re5 Re7 38. Nxf5 ({This is imprecise. Better was} 38. Kg1 $18) 38... Re8 ({Better chances for survival gave} 38... Nc6 {though also this loses:} 39. Nxe7 Nxe5 40. Nxd5+ exd5 41. Rxe5 Rc6 42. g4 $18) 39. Nd4 Re7 40. f5 Nb7 41. Rxe6+ Rexe6 42. Rxe6+ Rxe6 43. fxe6 Nd8 44. g4 Nxe6 45. Nxe6 Kxe6 46. d4 Kf6 47. h4 1-0


