1. d4 d5 2. c4 Nc6 3. e3 e5 4. dxe5 d4 5. exd4 ({Etwas besser ist wohl It is probably a little bit better to play} 5. a3 dxe3 (5... a5 6. Nf3 Bc5 7. exd4 Nxd4 8. Nc3 Bg4 9. Be2 Nxf3+ 10. Bxf3 Qxd1+ 11. Bxd1 Bxd1 12. Nxd1 Bd4 13. f4 f6 14. Be3 O-O-O 15. e6 f5 16. O-O Nf6 17. Bxd4 Rxd4 18. Ne3 g6 19. Rad1 Rxd1 20. Rxd1 Re8 21. Nd5 Rxe6 22. Nxf6 Rxf6 23. Rd5 b6 24. Kf2 Re6 25. Kf3 c6 26. Rd4 c5 27. Rd5 a4 28. h3 Re4 29. g4 Rxc4 30. gxf5 gxf5 31. Rxf5 Rc2 32. Rf7 Rxb2 33. f5 Kd8 34. f6 Ke8 35. Rxh7 b5 36. Ke4 b4 37. Kd5 bxa3 38. Re7+ Kf8 39. Re3 Rb3 40. Re2 Rb2 41. Re3 Rb3 42. Re4 Rb4 43. Re3 a2 44. Ra3 c4 45. Rxa2 c3 46. Rc2 {1/2-1/2 Franco Ocampo, Z-Miladinovic,I/Saint Vincent 1998/EXT 99 (46)} Rb3 {½-½ Franco Ocampo,Z-Miladinovic,I/Saint Vincent 1998/EXT 99 (46)}) 6. Qxd8+ Kxd8 7. Bxe3 Nxe5 8. Nc3 Be6 9. O-O-O+ Kc8 10. c5 Nf6 11. h3 a5 12. g4 h5 13. f4 Nc6 14. g5 Nd7 15. Ne4 a4 16. Bd3 Ra5 17. Bd2 Rxc5+ 18. Nxc5 Nxc5 19. Bc3 Bd6 20. Ne2 Re8 21. Bc2 Bc4 22. Nd4 Nxd4 23. Rxd4 b5 24. Re1 Rxe1+ 25. Bxe1 Ne6 26. Bf5 g6 27. Bxe6+ Bxe6 28. h4 Bc5 29. Rd3 Bf5 30. Rg3 Kd7 31. Rg2 Kc6 32. Bb4 Bb6 33. Re2 Kd5 34. Re5+ Kc4 35. Re7 Be6 36. f5 Bxf5 37. Rxf7 Be4 38. Kd2 c6 39. Bc3 Bg1 40. Be5 Kd5 41. Bc3 c5 42. Ke2 Bh2 43. Kf2 Bd6 44. Rb7 Kc4 45. Rb6 Bf4 46. Re6 Bc2 47. Kf3 Bc7 48. Re7 Bd6 49. Rd7 Kd5 50. Rd8 Ke6 51. Be1 Be5 52. Bg3 Bxb2 53. Rd6+ Kf7 54. Rd2 b4 55. axb4 a3 56. b5 a2 57. Rd7+ Ke8 58. Ra7 a1=Q 59. Rxa1 Bxa1 60. b6 Ba4 {0-1 Nikolic,P-Piket,J/Monaco 1996/CBM 52 ext (60) 0-1Nikolic,P-Piket,J/Monaco 1996/CBM 52 ext (60);}) ({Ein bei ungeübten Spielern beliebter Fehler ist A typical mistake at a lower level is to play} 5. Nf3 $2 Bb4+ 6. Bd2 dxe3 $1 7. fxe3 Bg4 {mit großem positionellen Vorteil für Schwarz, z.B. Black has a big positional advantage, for example:} 8. Bxb4 (8. Be2 Bxf3 9. Bxf3 Qh4+ 10. g3 Qxc4) 8... Qxd1+ 9. Kxd1 Nxb4 {nebst 10...0-0-0+. followed by 10...0-0-0+.}) 5... Qxd4 $1 6. Qxd4 Nxd4 7. Bd3 Bg4 $1 {Die schwarzen Figuren finden leicht ihre Bestimmungsorte; Weiß hingegen wird den Bauern e5 nicht halten können, die Löcher in der d-Linie (d3,d4) bleiben aber bestehen. It is easy for the black pieces to get on their squares of destination; whereas white will sooner or later lose the pawn on e5, and the gaps on the d-file ( d3, d4) still remain.} 8. f3 ({nicht Not} 8. Ne2 $4 Bxe2 $19) ({oder or} 8. Nc3 O-O-O 9. Be3 Nc6 $15) 8... Be6 9. Be3 O-O-O 10. Bxd4 Rxd4 11. Ke2 Ne7 12. Nd2 Ng6 13. Bxg6 hxg6 14. b3 Bf5 15. a3 Be7 16. Ra2 g5 17. Ke1 Rhd8 18. Ne2 Rd3 19. Ng3 Bg6 20. b4 Re3+ 21. Kf2 Rxe5 22. Re1 Rxe1 23. Kxe1 Bd3 24. Nge4 Rd4 25. c5 f5 26. Nf2 Bb5 27. Nf1 Bf6 28. Rd2 Rc4 29. Nd1 Rc1 30. Kf2 f4 31. g3 Bc3 32. Nxc3 Rxc3 33. Ra2 Bc4 34. Ra1 Rc2+ 35. Kg1 Bd5 0-1


