1. e4 {Marin,Mihail Marin,Mihail Marin,Mihail Marin,Mihail} e5 2. Nf3 Nc6 3. Bb5 Nf6 4. O-O Nxe4 5. d4 Be7 6. Qe2 Nd6 7. Bxc6 bxc6 8. dxe5 Nb7 9. Nc3 O-O 10. Re1 $1 Nc5 11. Nd4 Ne6 12. Be3 Nxd4 13. Bxd4 c5 14. Be3 d5 15. exd6 Bxd6 16. Rad1 (16. Ne4 {Tarrasch-Lasker, WM 1910/}) 16... Qf6 ({The move} 16... Qh4 {Marin,Mihail is underevaluated by theory because of the further evolution of the game where it was tried. Objectively speaking, this might be the best solution to Black's problems. If allowed to weaken the enemy kingside, Black should not refrain from doing so.} 17. h3 Bb7 $1 (17... Qb4 $6 18. Bc1 Be6 19. a3 Qb7 20. Qe4 $14 {Tarrasch,S-Lasker,E/Germany 1908/MainBase (½-½, 119)}) 18. b3 (18. Nb5 Ba6 19. c4 Bxb5 20. cxb5 Rab8 21. Bd2 Qa4 22. Bc3 Qxb5 23. Qg4 f6 $11) 18... a6 19. Nd5 Rae8 $11 {Black has achieved a harmonious regroupment of forces and enjoys satisfactory stability in the centre. The h4-queen keeps the enemy kingside under permanent pressure.}) (16... Bb7 $5 {(Marin,Mihail) Keres} 17. Bxc5 $2 Qg5 $1 $19) 17. Qh5 Rb8 18. Bc1 Qf5 19. Qxf5 Bxf5 20. Ne4 Rfe8 (20... Bxe4 21. Rxe4 Rb4 22. Rde1 h6 $11 {Marin,Mihail: 'ChessBase'}) 21. Nxd6 cxd6 22. Rxe8+ Rxe8 23. Be3 Re6 24. c3 a6 (24... a5 {Marin,Mihail: 'ChessBase' Marin,Mihail: '. Indeed, this seems to be a dead drawn position.'}) 25. b4 cxb4 26. cxb4 {Marin,Mihail: 'Now, White has some chances because of his queenside majority.'} h6 27. a4 Bc2 28. Ra1 Re4 29. b5 Rxa4 30. Rc1 Be4 31. b6 Kf8 $2 (31... Rb4 $11 {Marin,Mihail: 'ChessBase'}) 32. f3 $16 Bd5 33. Rc8+ Ke7 34. b7 Bxb7 35. Rc7+ Ke6 36. Rxb7 Ra1+ 37. Kf2 Ra2+ 38. Kg3 a5 (38... g5) 39. Ra7 $18 (39. h4) 39... a4 40. Ra6 g5 41. Bc5 Rd2 42. Ba7 f5 43. h4 f4+ 44. Kh3 Kf5 45. hxg5 hxg5 46. Rxa4 Rd1 47. g4+ fxg3 48. Kxg3 1-0


