ndre: '!' ChessBase: '!'} (42... Rf1 43. d5 $17) 43. Kf4 {Now the rook penetrates and the win is very simple.} ({JvR: 'The defence is prolonged by' Garry Kasparov: 'Only a little better was JvR: 'The defe'Only a little better was JvR: 'The defence is prolonged by' Schulz,Andre: 'Garry Kasparov: 'Only a little better was JvR: 'The defence is prolonged by'''' nce is prolonged by'' “Only a little better was} 43. Kd2 $142 {Garry Kasparov: ''' ChessBase: '''''' ChessBase: '' Schulz,Andre: '' Schulz,Andre: 'Garry Kasparov: ''''''} Rg6 (43... Rh6 44. h4 Rg6 45. d5 Bxd5 46. Be5 f6 47. Bd6 b3 $17) 44. g4 ({or “} 44. d5 $1 Bxd5 45. Be5 {, but even here Black should win after} Bc6 46. Bd4 Bxb5 47. axb5 Rxg3 48. h4 Rg4 {” - Nunn}) 44... Rh6 $19 {Garry Kasparov: ''-+' ChessBase: '-+''''-+' ChessBase: '-+' Schulz,Andre: '-+' Schulz,Andre: 'Garry Kasparov: ''-+'''' Alekhine ” (Kasparov).} 45. a5 {JvR} Rxh3 46. a6 Rh2+ 47. Kc1 Rh1+ 48. Kd2 Rd1+ 49. Ke3 Rb1 50. a7 Bd5) ({If} 43. Kf3 {instead, then naturally Black plays} Bd1+ {. and 44...Re2.}) 43... Re2 {'-+'} 44. Bc1 Rc2 45. Be3 Bd5 {Garry Kasparov: '. After this important win Lasker scored a further 5½ out of 6(!), and Capa was not able to keep pace with him... JvR: 'Lopez : 'Now we see what Black's maneuvering was all about. He's now controlling two of the three squares the b4-pawn must traverse on its way to promotion. The promotion square can't be guarded by a White piece (the Bishop is shut out from ever defending b1). Reti sees that the b-pawn is now unstoppable and resigns.''''. After this important win Lasker scored a further 5½ out of 6(!), and Capa was not able to keep pace with him... JvR: 'Lopez : 'Now we see what Black's maneuvering was all about. He's now controlling two of the three squares the b4-pawn must traverse on its way to promotion. The promotion square can't be guarded by a White piece (the Bishop is shut out from ever defending b1). Reti sees that the b-pawn is now unstoppable and resigns.'' Schulz,An