{[%mdl 8256]} 1. d4 d5 {Opening = D10 - Damengambit-Slawische Verteidigung /Queen's Gambit-Slav Defen} 2. c4 c6 3. e3 Nf6 4. Nc3 Qb6 {last book move} 5. Bd3 Bg4 6. Qa4 {Keene: '?!'} e6 7. c5 Qc7 8. b4 Nbd7 9. f4 Be7 10. Nf3 Bxf3 {Keene: '!'} 11. gxf3 Nh5 12. Bd2 O-O 13. Ne2 f5 14. Ng3 Nhf6 15. O-O-O $15 (15. Rg1 $5 $14) (15. O-O Kh8 $1 16. Kh1 Rg8 { ...g5}) 15... b6 16. Qc2 $17 (16. Qa6 $5 $15) 16... a5 17. Rdg1 axb4 18. Bxf5 exf5 19. Nxf5 Rf7 20. Nh6+ Kf8 21. Nxf7 Kxf7 (21... bxc5 22. Ng5 Qa5 23. Ne6+ Kf7 24. f5 $11) 22. e4 (22. Bxb4 bxc5 23. dxc5 Qa7 $19) 22... bxc5 23. e5 cxd4 {Keene: '!'} (23... Ng8 24. Qxh7 $18) 24. exf6 (24. e6+ Kf8 25. exd7 Qxd7 $19) 24... Nxf6 25. Rg2 Qd6 26. Rhg1 Bf8 27. h4 Ra3 {Black gets strong initiative} 28. h5 (28. Kb1 $19) 28... b3 $1 (28... Nxh5 29. Qxh7 Qh6 30. Qf5+ Nf6 31. Qe5 Rxa2 32. f5 $14) 29. Qb2 bxa2 {The passed pawn on a2 quickly leads to threats. Do you see the mate threat?.} 30. Qb7+ Qd7 31. Qxd7+ Nxd7 {Threatening mate... how? Keene: '-+'} 32. Kb2 Nb6 33. Ka1 Rxf3 {Keene: '?'} (33... c5 $1 $19) 34. Kxa2 Nc4 35. Bc1 Kf6 (35... Ne3 36. Rb2 $19) 36. Rd1 Ba3 37. Bxa3 Rxa3+ 38. Kb1 Rb3+ 39. Ka2 {½-½ (57) Reti,R (2550)-Nimzowitsch,A (2550) Goteborg 1920 [Fritz 5.00 (5s)] ½-½ (57) Reti,R-Nimzowitsch,A Goteborg 1920 [Keene]} Ra3+ $4 $11 (39... Rh3 $142 40. Rg5 Rh2+ 41. Ka1 Nd2 $19) 40. Kb1 Ne3 41. Rg3 c5 42. Rd2 Ra6 (42... Rb3+ 43. Rb2 Rxb2+ 44. Kxb2 $19) 43. Rb2 Re6 {Keene: '?'} (43... c4 {Keene: '-+!' '-+!'} 44. Rb7 c3 45. Rc7 $19) 44. Rb7 Nf5 45. Ra3 c4 46. Ra8 {Threatening mate... how? Threatening mate: Rf8} Re1+ 47. Ka2 Re2+ 48. Kb1 d3 {Keene: '??'} (48... Ne7 $5 $17 {Keene: '-+!' '-+!'}) 49. Rf8+ {Keene: '=!'} Ke6 50. Rb6+ Ke7 51. Rxf5 Re1+ 52. Kb2 d2 53. Rxd5 d1=Q {Threatening mate: Qc1} 54. Rb7+ Ke8 $14 (54... Kf6 55. Rb6+ Kf7 56. Rb7+ Kf8 57. Rb8+ Ke7 58. Rb7+ Kf6 59. Rb6+ Ke7 60. Rb7+ $11) 55. Rb8+ $11 (55. Rxd1 Rxd1 56. Rxg7 h6 $11) 55... Ke7 {The mate threat is Qc1 The mate threat is Qc1 ½-½ (57) Reti,R (2550)-Nimzowitsch,A (2550) Goteborg 1920 [Fritz 5.00 (5s)] ½-½ (57) Reti,R-Nimzowitsch,A Goteborg 1920 [Keene]} 56. Rb7+ Kf6 57. Rb6+ {Keene: ''At that time I was still suffering from the effects of the psychic oppression of the post-war period...' - Nimzowitsch.'} 1/2-1/2


