ve piece. Lasker plays consistently for activity and in particular to expose the white king, even if this costs him a pawn or two.'} 24. Kh2 {'?!' 'h1' JvR: '!?' Garry Kasparov: '?!' '?!' '?!' Garry Kasparov: ''The beginning of an artificial manoeuvre, the insufficiency of which is demonstrated by Dr Lasker with marvellous clearness an''The beginning of an artificial manoeuvre, the insufficiency of which is demonstrated by Dr Lasker with marvellous clearness and precision. h1 JvR: '!?' '!?' Schulz,Andre: '?!' 'Garry Kasparov: ''The beginning of an artificial manoeuvre, the insufficiency of which is demonstrated by Dr Lasker with marvellous clearness and precision. h1 JvR: '!?' '!?'''' d precision. h1 JvR: '!?' '!?'' ChessBase: '?!' '?!' '?!' '?!' “The beginning of an artificial manoeuvre, the insufficiency of which is demonstrated by Dr. Lasker with marvellous clearness and precision,” commented Alekhine. EXERCISE: The position still isn't advantageous for Black, but it's a fighting position, where the priority is to set the opponent problems. What move enabled Lasker make progress in this respect? ANSWER: '?!' Nunn John, Game 25: 'White plans Qh1 to step up the pressure against the d5-pawn, but Lasker is prepared to sacrifice this pawn in order to seize the initiative. Maddox: '?!'' Garry Kasparov: ''The beginning of an artificial manoeuvre, the insufficiency of which is demonstrated by Dr Lasker with marvellous clearness and precision.' Garry Kasparov: 'Schulz,Andre: 'h1'' Nunn John, Game 25: 'Maddox: 'Planning to shift the queen to h1, adding to the pressure on d5.'' Nunn John, Game 25: 'Maddox: 'Mit der Idee, die Dame nach h1 zu führen, um den Druck auf d5 zu verstärken.''} ({Garry Kasparov: 'Better drawing chances were offered by''Better drawing chances were offered by Schulz,Andre: 'Garry Kasparov: 'Better drawing chances were offered by''' A better chance was Nunn John, Game 25: 'Better is' Nunn John, Game 25: 'Besser ist'} 24. Nb5 $132 {d4,c3×d5