d resigns.''''' . The b-pawn decides proceedings. Now since Black can't be stopped from queening his b-pawn...White resigns. Nunn John, Game 25: 'Now there's no stopping the b-pawn.' Garry Kasparov: '. After this important win Lasker scored a further 51/2 out of 6(!), and Capa was not able to keep pace with him...'} 0-1


