 the Black King '}) 13. Qe1 {JvR: '!' JvR: '24: Security of the King: '!' 'Not only defending against Black's ... Bf4, but also renewing his own threat of Nxf5'' 24: Security of the King: 'Not only defending against Black's ... f4, but also renewing his own threat of xf5 '} (13. Kb1 {!?} O-O 14. d5 Bf4 15. Qd4) 13... Nc6 {JvR: '?' 24: Security of the King: '?'} (13... Qf4+ {24: Security of the King: ''} 14. Kb1 Nc6 {JvR: '(Alekhine)' '' 24: Security of the King: '(Alekhine) '} 15. Nb5 $16) ({Less risks are taken by} 13... O-O {JvR !?} 14. d5 Re8 15. Be2 a5 16. Kb1 Na6 17. dxe6 fxe6 18. Nb5 $14) 14. Nxf5 $1 {!} Qf4+ 15. Ne3 Nxd4 16. g3 Qe5 17. Bg2 {JvR: 'White exerts distant pressure by his queen and bishop.'} Nc6 {JvR: '?'} (17... Bc6 18. f4 (18. Bxc6+ {JvR} Nxc6 19. f4 Qg7 20. Nf5 Qf8 21. Nxd6+ cxd6 22. Nb5 O-O-O 23. Qc3 $1 {Fork ... exhibits power of the Queen '' Alekhine 24: Security of the King: 'Fork ... exhibits power of the Queen '} Kb8 24. Nxd6 Rxd6 25. Rxd6 Qxd6 26. Qxh8+) 18... Qg7 (18... Qf6 19. Bxc6+ Nxc6 20. Ne4 $14) 19. Bxc6+ bxc6 20. Nc4 Rd8 21. Qe4 c5 22. Qb7 O-O 23. Rhe1 $16) ({JvR: 'The ending after'} 17... O-O-O $5 {JvR: '(Alekhine)' !?} 18. f4 (18. Nc4 {JvR} Qxe1 (18... Qg7) 19. Rhxe1 Nf5 {offers chances of survival.}) 18... Qg7 19. Nc4 Bc5 20. Na5 Bc6 21. Nxc6 Nxc6 22. Bxc6 bxc6 23. Qe4 Kb7 $16 {und Schwarz verbleibt auch hier mit einer sehr undankbaren Stellung.}) 18. f4 (18. Nc4 {!} Qh5 19. Nxd6+ cxd6 20. Rxd6 O-O-O 21. f4 e5 22. Qe4 $18) 18... Qg7 {?} (18... Qh5 {!} 19. Ne4 Be7 20. Nd5 O-O-O) 19. Nb5 {JvR: '!' '+-' 24: Security of the King: '!'} (19. Nf5 {JvR} Bxf4+ {Move order is important 24: Security of the King: 'Move order is important '}) 19... O-O {JvR: 'Black has to lose a pawn. 24: Security of the King: 'At long last the Black king finds a safer place, but at the cost of a pawn, and now White holds the advantage positionally'' 24: Security of the King: 'At long last the Black king finds a safer place, but at the cost of a pawn, 